    // the MAIN thread (the worker only drives the timer), so a frozen event
    // loop stops it exactly like LATENCY — but its FLAGS additionally prove
    // the RENDER loop is alive, catching the event-loop-alive/render-dead gap
    // (WebGL context loss, rAF stall) that LATENCY can't see. bit0=rendered
    // recently, bit1=tab hidden (server treats hidden as render-OK so a
